 7: # Coordinate Converter — HTML Architecture Guardrails
 8: 
 9: ## Canonical file / scope
10: - The canonical app lives in a **single** HTML file (currently: `coordinate_converter Claude.html`).
11: - Keep changes surgical and consistent with the existing patterns in that file.
12: 
13: ## State, persistence, and invariants
14: - Centralized app state object: `state`.
15: - Persistence via localStorage key: `coordconv_v1`.
16: - IndexedDB is used for offline map tile pack and some geo caches.
17: - On load, persisted data must be **sanitized/clamped** (numbers, string length, arrays caps). Do not trust localStorage content.
18: 
19: ## Map + offline behavior
20: - The mini-map must be usable even with no active conversion:
21:   - Default startup center is **La Spezia** fallback (no silent GPS at startup).
22: - Offline behavior:
23:   - When effectively offline, prefer rendering cached tiles from IndexedDB and show placeholders for missing tiles.
24:   - Do not introduce an automatic “online fallback” that defeats the user’s offline/OPSEC choices.
25: 
26: ## Geolocation UX (opt-in only)
27: - Geolocation must be **explicit opt-in** via UI actions (no automatic `getCurrentPosition()` on page load).
28: - Respect secure context constraints (`window.isSecureContext`): if not secure, disable geo UI and explain why.
29: - Live tracking uses `watchPosition` and must be stoppable; avoid spamming history during live ticks.
30: 
31: ## Rendering and history
32: - `renderResults(lat, lon, meta, opts)` supports an option like `{ skipHistory: true }` used for:
33:   - live tracking updates after the first fix
34:   - language re-apply / UI rerender that must not duplicate history
35: 
36: ## i18n
37: - i18n dictionary exists inline (IT/EN/FR).
38: - There is both:
39:   - `data-i18n` → updates via `textContent` (default, safe)
40:   - `data-i18n-html` → updates via `innerHTML` (only for explicitly allowed rich-text help content)
41: - Do not expand `innerHTML` usage beyond the intended rich-text areas.
42: 
43: ## Event handlers / cleanup
44: - Handlers for map tools (bbox draw, draggable panels, pick modes) are designed to be **idempotent** (install once) and provide explicit cleanup on cancel/Esc.
45: - Do not add listeners in hot paths without a cleanup plan.
</file>

