 5: 
 6: # Coordinate Converter — Domain Knowledge (On Demand)
 7: 
 8: ## Coordinate / GIS domain
 9: - App is a lightweight GIS tool: parsing + conversions + mini-map + tools.
10: - Coordinate formats include: WGS84 (DD/DDM/DMS), UTM, MGRS, Plus Codes.
11: - There are Italian datums and additional datum support introduced later (see below).
12: 
13: ## Datum / CRS additions (implemented)
14: - Extra datum section exists in results (collapsible):
15:   - NAD27 / NAD83 / OSGB36 / CH1903 / SK42 (as implemented in the HTML).
16: - Auto-detect extended for:
17:   - BNG (British National Grid)
18:   - SK42 Gauss–Krüger
19: - Export toggle exists to include datum extras as metadata/extensions in GPX/KML/GeoJSON.
20: 
21: ## DTG NATO (Date-Time Group)
22: - Full support for DTG format: `DDHHMMZMMMYY` (e.g. `211630ZAPR26`).
23: - Parsing/formatting is implemented without external deps; `J` timezone letter is intentionally rejected.
24: - Keyboard shortcuts prefer `Alt+T` / `Alt+Shift+T` due to browser conflicts with `Ctrl+T`.
25: - DTG is stored as **Zulu** in history/favorites/exports to avoid ambiguity.
26: 
27: ## Geocoding (OPSEC-aware)
28: - Forward geocoding and reverse geocoding exist, using Nominatim.
29: - Strict/OPSEC mode exists (`state.opsecStrict`): must block any external fetch.
30: - Defensive UX patterns:
31:   - geocode UI is closed by default; opening implies consent to read the disclaimer
32:   - no silent exfiltration: non-coordinate paste prompts explicit `confirm()` before searching online
33: - Resilience:
34:   - client-side rate limiting (≈ 1 request / second)
35:   - retry with backoff
36:   - circuit breaker (temporary lockout after repeated failures)
37: - Offline fallback exists via a small built-in cities dataset + optional user-imported JSON stored in IDB.
38: 
39: ## Offline map tiles / coverage overlay
40: - IndexedDB tile pack exists; when offline, the mini-map renders cached tiles and uses placeholders for missing tiles.
41: - Coverage overlay exists:
42:   - per-tile green tint when tile is served from IDB cache
43:   - named areas overlay rectangles with zoom-range signaling
44: - Named areas include bbox + optional zoom range `z0..z1` (legacy entries without `z0/z1` must keep working).
45: - Offline panel can dock/floating depending on map size; it can be draggable in full mode.
46: - Deleting a named area can optionally delete tiles from IDB (supports wiping both map layers if layer is not tracked per pack).
47: 
48: ## Tools drawer / navigation hub
49: - Tools drawer is a navigation hub: it scrolls to existing `<details>` tool sections in `<main>` and flashes/highlights them.
50: - Do not refactor it into a “workspace drawer”; keep main sections in the DOM.
51: 
52: ## Track builder
53: - Track builder exists with:
54:   - add current result, click map pick mode, paste list, import GPX/KML/GeoJSON
55:   - export GPX/KML/GeoJSON/CSV
56: - `Esc` exits pick modes before doing global clear actions.
57: 
58: ## Map measurement
59: - On-map measurement supports:
60:   - line (distance + azimuth)
61:   - polygon (perimeter + area)
62:   - drag handles + right-click delete
63:   - units (m/km/nm/mi/ft) persisted in storage
</file>

